title: "fix(diagrams): eliminate loading flash on Ferris commercial mower model selection"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: high
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("it's doing this flashy flash s***. I don't know what that is.
    Ola knows exactly what that is and he's going to fix it")
  - meetup-02-06-26 (timestamp ~00:55:39 — selecting a Ferris commercial mower config)
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]

impact: |
  John demoed Ferris to the team and the immediate visible defect was a visual flash
  when selecting a commercial mower configuration number. This happens in front of
  ownership at the Friday presentation. It undermines confidence in the whole platform
  even if everything else works.

description: |
  Reproduce: /parts-diagrams/ferris → Commercial Mowers → select a 59-series config.
  Expected: smooth navigation/load to model assembly list or schematic.
  Actual: visual flash/flicker before the page content settles.

  Common root causes in Next.js App Router:
  1. Client-side navigation triggers a React Suspense boundary that shows a
     fallback (usually `loading.tsx` or a Suspense fallback) before the data resolves.
     Fix: ensure the loading skeleton matches the page layout so the flash is invisible.
  2. CSS-in-JS or Tailwind class mismatch on initial hydration (SSR vs client mismatch).
     Look for dynamic className that differs between server and client render.
  3. `useEffect` that changes layout-affecting state on mount (e.g., visibility toggle).
  4. An image that loads after layout (LCP shift). Check if the brand hero or TypeCard
     images cause layout shift (use priority={true} for above-fold images).
  5. The assembly list page fetches BOM data client-side and briefly shows empty state.

  Investigate in this order:
  - Open DevTools → Performance tab → record navigation to the Ferris model page.
  - Identify which element flashes (the whole page? specific section? image?).
  - Check `app/parts-diagrams/loading.tsx` and any `Suspense` in BrandModelGroups.
  - Check `BrandModelGroups` and `assembly-list-layout.tsx` for client-only state
    that runs after hydration.

scope:
  in:
    - Root-cause the flash (specific element + trigger)
    - Fix: loading skeleton or eliminating the flash-causing state change
    - Verify: no flash on Ferris → commercial mower → model selection at 4G throttle
  out:
    - Full page skeleton redesign
    - Changing the data-fetching model

invariants:
  - No React.memo / unjustified useMemo/useCallback (React Compiler handles it)
  - loading.tsx skeleton must match actual page layout dimensions to prevent CLS

acceptance:
  - Navigate: /parts-diagrams/ferris → Commercial Mowers → select any 59-series model
  - No visible flash or layout shift during the transition (Chrome DevTools CLS ≈ 0)
  - Same test passes on mobile (375px, 4G throttle)
  - Existing Playwright tests do not regress

dep: A3 (need Ferris routes working before this can be reproduced cleanly)
output: loading.tsx fix + any Suspense/skeleton adjustments in the affected page
